==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From Middle English [[helthe]], from Old English [[hælþ|hǣlþ]].

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛlθ|-ɛlθ]]

===Noun===
'''health'''

# The [[state]] of being free of [[physical]] or [[psychological]] [[disease]], [[illness]], or [[malfunction]].
# Physical [[condition]].
# Emotional condition.
# Well-being, [[wellness]].
# A [[toast]] to [[prosperity]].
#: Example: ''To your health!''

